  <h2>Random Integer Generator</h2>


  <p>This form allows you to generate random integers.  The randomness
  comes from atmospheric noise, which for many purposes is better than
  the pseudo-random number algorithms typically used in computer
  programs.</p>

  <form method=3D"get" action=3D"https://www.random.org/integers/">

  <h3>Part 1: The Integers</h3>

  <p>Generate <input type=3D"text" name=3D"num" value=3D"100" size=3D"6" ma=
xlength=3D"12"> random integers (maximum 10,000).</p>

  <p>Each integer should have a value between <input type=3D"text" name=3D"=
min" value=3D"1" size=3D"6" maxlength=3D"12"> and <input type=3D"text" name=
=3D"max" value=3D"100" size=3D"6" maxlength=3D"12">
  (both inclusive; limits =C2=B11,000,000,000).</p>

  <p>Format in <input type=3D"text" name=3D"col" value=3D"5" size=3D"2" max=
length=3D"6"> column(s).</p>

 =20
 =20
 =20

  <h3>Part 2: Go!</h3>

  <p>Be patient!  It may take a little while to generate your numbers...</p=
>

  <p>
    <input type=3D"submit" value=3D"Get Numbers">
    <input type=3D"reset" value=3D"Reset Form">
    <input type=3D"button" class=3D"indented" value=3D"Switch to Advanced M=
ode">
  </p>

  </form>

  <p>Need more numbers than this form supports? Check out our <a href=3D"ht=
tps://files.random.org/">File Generation Service</a>.</p>

  <p>Note: The numbers generated with this form will be picked
  independently of each other (like rolls of a die) and may therefore
  contain duplicates.  There is also the <a href=3D"https://www.random.org/=
sequences/">Sequence Generator</a>, which generates
  randomized sequences (like raffle tickets drawn from a hat) and
  where each number can only occur once.</p>


  <p></p>
